01:01:21.010 --> 01:01:23.590
And the floor is open.

01:01:23.590 --> 01:01:28.360
Let me just add one thing
in the context of exile,

01:01:28.360 --> 01:01:29.710
and that is the contributions

01:01:29.710 --> 01:01:34.180
that exiles themselves have
done, have made to the countries

01:01:34.180 --> 01:01:37.330
that have hosted them.

01:01:37.330 --> 01:01:41.480
And since Juan eloquently
spoke about Spain,

01:01:41.480 --> 01:01:44.770
what would El Colegio
de Mexico be.

01:01:44.770 --> 01:01:48.980
What would be the
publishing industry in Mexico

01:01:48.980 --> 01:01:55.160
and in Argentina without the
contribution of Spanish exiles.

01:01:55.160 --> 01:01:58.330
So this is an entirely
dynamic process

01:01:58.330 --> 01:02:01.560
that we have to take
into account.

01:02:01.560 --> 01:02:05.380
And, obviously, the
issue of repatriation,

01:02:05.380 --> 01:02:08.160
the issue of return,
the issue of recognition

01:02:08.160 --> 01:02:11.610
of exiles once they return
home when they are allowed

01:02:11.610 --> 01:02:17.150
to return home, the flag that
justice has not been meted

01:02:17.150 --> 01:02:21.700
out equally in each of these
countries, that the process

01:02:21.700 --> 01:02:26.930
of returning was radically
different in each one of them.

01:02:26.930 --> 01:02:32.560
The flag that Spain still
refuses to address major issues

01:02:32.560 --> 01:02:37.600
such as unearthing the tombs of
those who were executed during

01:02:37.600 --> 01:02:39.140
and after the Spanish Civil War.

01:02:39.140 --> 01:02:44.270
These are issues that affect
us all in one way or another

01:02:44.270 --> 01:02:47.990
and I-- They do address
some of the keywords

01:02:47.990 --> 01:02:51.000
that appear in this book.

01:02:51.000 --> 01:02:56.780
So hopefully we opened up
something beyond addressing some

01:02:56.780 --> 01:02:59.090
of the issues that we wanted

01:02:59.090 --> 01:03:03.750
to incorporate into
this first book.

