going to say something else.

01:32:28.930 --> 01:32:30.230
&gt;&gt; Juan Uriagereka:
Well, I was just going

01:32:30.230 --> 01:32:31.590
to say a footnote on that.

01:32:31.590 --> 01:32:34.820
Those are the people I
know for two reasons.

01:32:34.820 --> 01:32:36.710
A, because many of
them came to Spain.

01:32:36.710 --> 01:32:39.280
B, because I was a working
class kid so they lived

01:32:39.280 --> 01:32:40.750
in working class neighborhoods.

01:32:40.750 --> 01:32:44.140
In fact we faced very similar
problems including drug

01:32:44.140 --> 01:32:47.250
addiction and things like
that but they had a level

01:32:47.250 --> 01:32:49.960
of education that I
certainly didn't have.

01:32:49.960 --> 01:32:52.320
So the reason they
taught us many things is

01:32:52.320 --> 01:32:53.620
because they could.

01:32:53.620 --> 01:32:58.760
Kind of like when this teacher
was internally exiled by Franco,

01:32:58.760 --> 01:33:01.660
my mother learned how to read
from somebody with more culture.

01:33:01.660 --> 01:33:02.960
So these are interesting,

01:33:02.960 --> 01:33:05.060
unintended consequences
of these dynamics.

01:33:05.060 --> 01:33:06.360
Yeah.

01:33:06.360 --> 01:33:07.660
&gt;&gt; Saúl Sosnowski:
Yup, absolutely.

01:33:07.660 --> 01:33:08.960
Yeah.

